Three data periods are used. Each serves a distinct purpose. All windows end on today's date.
All computations use log(price) throughout.

Each window estimates its own α and β independently via OLS — no cross-window parameter sharing.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
STEP 1 — I(1) PREREQUISITE CHECK  |  Data period: PAST 5 YEARS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

For each series, run two ADF tests on log(price):
  (a) Level test:      adfuller(log_price, autolag='AIC')
  (b) Difference test: adfuller(log_price.diff().dropna(), autolag='AIC')   [= log returns]

A series is I(1) if BOTH conditions hold:
  • Level p > 0.05 — log price is non-stationary ✓
  • Diff  p < 0.05 — log returns are stationary  ✓

Display as a compact banner:
  • Both I(1) → green success banner, show level and diff p-values for each ticker.
  • Level non-stationary but diff also non-stationary (may be I(2)) → amber warning; still proceed.
  • Level stationary (unusual) → amber warning; still proceed.

autolag='AIC' is used for all adfuller() calls throughout the module.


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
STEP 2a — 5-YEAR EG TEST  (long-run reference)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Regression on 5-year log prices:   log(Y) = α₅ + β₅ · log(X) + ε

Run OLS in BOTH directions (A=Y, B=X) and (B=Y, A=X) on the 5-year data.
For each direction: estimate α₅, β₅ → compute residuals → ADF(residuals, autolag='AIC').
Cointegrated = p < 0.05.

Primary direction = lower 5yr p-value.

Show two spread charts (primary ★ and reverse) each containing:
  - Log-price spread (residuals) over time with ±1σ bands and mean line
  - α₅, β₅ metrics
  - ADF test statistic, p-value, critical values (1%/5%/10%)
  - Verdict: Cointegrated ✓ or Not cointegrated ✗
  - Chart title: Spread (5yr): TICKER_Y→TICKER_X  [Mon YYYY → Mon YYYY]

Label each direction: "TICKER_Y (Y) regressed on TICKER_X (X)"


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
STEP 2b — 2-YEAR EG TEST  (recent confirmation + β comparison)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Regression on 2-year log prices:   log(Y) = α₂ + β₂ · log(X) + ε

Fresh OLS on 2-year data — α₂ and β₂ are re-estimated independently (NOT fixed from 5yr).
Run in BOTH directions; show both p-values. Primary direction = lower 2yr p-value (may differ
from the 5yr primary direction).

Show two spread charts (same format as 5yr), then a β Comparison block:

  β Comparison: 5yr vs 2yr OLS
  ┌────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────┬────────┐
  │ Direction          │ β (5yr)  │ β (2yr)  │ Change │
  ├────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────┼────────┤
  │ A (Y) → B (X)     │  β₅_AB   │  β₂_AB   │  Δ     │
  │ B (Y) → A (X)     │  β₅_BA   │  β₂_BA   │  Δ     │
  └────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────┴────────┘

A large or persistent β shift suggests structural drift in the relationship.


