STABILITY DIAGNOSTICS — Rolling β Chart
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Computed separately from the EG tests. Uses 5-year history in the primary direction.

Rolling 252-day OLS β for log(Y) = α + β · log(X):
  At each date t: regress log(Y_{t-251:t}) on log(X_{t-251:t}) → record β_t.

Chart:
  - Rolling β line over 5-year history
  - Fixed 5yr β (from the 5yr EG OLS) as a red dashed reference line
  - ±1σ bands of the rolling β distribution (gray dotted)

Summary metrics below chart:
  Fixed 5yr β | Rolling β Mean | Rolling β Std | Rolling β Range (min → max)

Purpose: reveal hedge ratio volatility, structural breaks, regime shifts over time.
Displayed as "Stability Diagnostics" section in the Cointegration tab, below the Final Verdict.
